Key Match Events: Kevin Durant scored 14 of his 25 points in the fourth quarter and overtime, including a jumper with 21 seconds remaining in regulation that tied the game at 103 and forced the overtime period.
Post-Match Reflections: Kevin Durant admitted that 'The Wall' at the Intuit Dome was a distraction when he missed two free throws in the fourth quarter when his team was trailing by four points.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Intuit Dome, home of the Los Angeles Clippers, features a unique section called 'The Wall' with 51 consecutive rows of seats, where diehard Clippers fans can sit and get a vetting process to get tickets.
